WEBVTT

02:01.621 --> 02:03.123
I'm sorry,

02:04.332 --> 02:05.792
Itadori.

02:09.170 --> 02:10.046
<i>Damn it.</i>

02:43.121 --> 02:46.623
<i>Such speed.
I can’t tell what kind of technique it is.</i>

02:46.624 --> 02:51.003
<i>At this level of overwhelming pressure,
there’s nothing for him to reveal.</i>

02:51.004 --> 02:53.298
<i>This isn’t even a matter
of Convergence anymore!</i>

02:54.591 --> 02:57.719
<i>The Blood Manipulation outside my body
isn’t working at all.</i>

03:07.770 --> 03:10.899
So persistent. Seriously, what are you?

03:11.858 --> 03:14.694
A brother. A brother of ten.

03:16.029 --> 03:18.572
<i>Flowing Red Scale, stack.</i>

03:18.573 --> 03:21.074
That doesn’t answer my question.

03:21.075 --> 03:22.951
I’m asking about that technique

03:22.952 --> 03:25.747
and that ridiculous toughness of yours.

03:43.848 --> 03:45.767
<i>He matched my timing.</i>

03:53.191 --> 03:56.778
I see. Flowing Red Scale, huh?

03:57.403 --> 04:00.030
You’re concentrating that power
into your eye muscles,

04:00.031 --> 04:02.116
boosting your dynamic visual acuity!

04:03.326 --> 04:07.330
Too bad. I’m moving
with counters in mind from the start.

04:08.373 --> 04:11.792
You’re so persistent,
so I figured I would use this.

04:11.793 --> 04:14.336
A weapon. You use Blood Manipulation,
so stopping the bleeding

04:14.337 --> 04:15.546
should be easy, right?

04:16.089 --> 04:19.424
Let’s see how long
you can keep fighting me

04:19.425 --> 04:21.010
while managing hemostasis.

04:21.594 --> 04:22.719
Always prepared, huh?

04:22.720 --> 04:26.515
Keep it a secret, yeah?
Honestly, I think it’s lame.

04:26.516 --> 04:29.017
Sorcerers carrying weapons around.

04:29.018 --> 04:31.603
They need one to win.

04:31.604 --> 04:34.731
There are more like them
than you would expect.

04:34.732 --> 04:38.318
My older brothers are a disgrace too,
wandering around uselessly.

04:38.319 --> 04:41.738
Hard to believe they ever had the nerve
to badmouth Toji.

04:41.739 --> 04:44.200
You really hate your siblings, huh?

04:44.701 --> 04:46.410
I do hate them.

04:46.411 --> 04:49.955
A big brother who’s worse than
his little brother has no reason to exist.

04:49.956 --> 04:52.165
They should just hang themselves and die.

04:52.166 --> 04:54.294
Maybe it’s thanks to those brothers

04:54.919 --> 04:57.213
that you’re who you are today.

04:58.798 --> 05:02.426
Did you just say something
extremely creepy?

05:02.427 --> 05:03.761
That seriously grossed me out.

05:05.305 --> 05:07.597
Whether he’s capable or not,
an older brother

05:07.598 --> 05:09.475
is a role model for his younger siblings.

05:10.476 --> 05:12.394
If I go down the wrong path,

05:12.395 --> 05:14.605
my younger brother should avoid it.

05:15.189 --> 05:19.610
If I walk the right path,
he should follow.

05:20.236 --> 05:24.615
What if the reason you’re strong
is because your brothers were weak?

05:25.450 --> 05:27.827
You asked
why I’m so persistent, didn’t you?

05:28.411 --> 05:31.455
I’ll tell you. I don’t have a role model.

05:31.456 --> 05:33.457
I make mistakes over and over again.

05:33.458 --> 05:37.670
Even so, I have to keep walking
ahead of my younger brother.

05:38.171 --> 05:39.630
That’s why I’m strong.

05:44.510 --> 05:48.139
<i>What does that mean? How are you alive
after losing this much blood?</i>

05:56.022 --> 05:59.900
<i>The Death Painting Wombs
are hybrids of curses and humans.</i>

05:59.901 --> 06:03.988
<i>They possess a unique constitution
that converts cursed energy into blood.</i>

06:04.489 --> 06:08.785
<i>As long as their cursed energy lasts,
blood loss won’t kill them.</i>

06:35.144 --> 06:36.686
<i>My legs feel heavy.</i>

06:36.687 --> 06:40.108
<i>I'm glued to the blood
that's soaked into the ground?</i>

06:41.275 --> 06:42.485
You know the rest.

06:43.861 --> 06:45.113
Checkmate.

06:51.327 --> 06:53.162
We’ll see.

06:54.580 --> 06:57.791
<i>My technique traces movements
that were created in advance</i>

06:57.792 --> 06:59.210
<i>at 24 frames per second.</i>

06:59.794 --> 07:02.713
<i>If that's all he has to slow me down,
I can still move without any problem.</i>

07:03.798 --> 07:05.091
<i>Try it.</i>

07:09.428 --> 07:11.431
<i>Why aren’t you shooting?</i>

07:11.931 --> 07:13.807
<i>This was the result of 150 years</i>

07:13.808 --> 07:16.768
<i>spent constantly facing his own technique.</i>

07:16.769 --> 07:18.521
<i>Choso’s original.</i>

07:44.046 --> 07:48.926
Sorry, but I can’t understand
someone who couldn’t love their siblings.

08:04.233 --> 08:05.234
What?

08:11.449 --> 08:13.159
Looks like you had a rough time,

08:14.577 --> 08:15.536
Naoya.

08:19.707 --> 08:21.417
Don’t look down on me.

08:27.757 --> 08:30.051
<i>What the hell is this? Poison?</i>

08:30.885 --> 08:33.137
<i>Red Blood Manipulation
doesn’t have that kind of effect…</i>

08:33.721 --> 08:36.307
<i>No, this isn’t an effect of his technique.</i>

08:36.807 --> 08:40.477
<i>That amount of blood…
He wasn’t human to begin with!</i>

08:40.478 --> 08:42.187
<i>An incarnated body…</i>

08:42.188 --> 08:45.857
<i>Inhuman blood is mixed in,
and the body is rejecting it!</i>

08:45.858 --> 08:47.401
Shall I heal you?

08:48.778 --> 08:50.862
My reverse cursed technique

08:50.863 --> 08:52.240
can heal other people too.

08:52.823 --> 08:54.033
But in return,

08:54.659 --> 08:58.203
please report Itadori’s death

08:58.204 --> 08:59.956
to the higher-ups yourself.

09:03.084 --> 09:06.420
<i>Jin…</i>

09:10.258 --> 09:11.676
What is it, Dad?

09:12.760 --> 09:14.971
If you’re going to talk about her,
I’m leaving.

09:16.264 --> 09:20.601
Jin. How you live your life
is your choice.

09:21.394 --> 09:24.813
But stay away from that woman.

09:24.814 --> 09:25.982
You’ll die.

09:26.983 --> 09:30.027
Please don’t talk about weird stuff
in front of Yuji.

09:30.528 --> 09:33.698
Apparently, babies remember
more than you would think.

09:34.198 --> 09:36.950
I know you wanted a child,

09:36.951 --> 09:40.496
and that Kaori couldn't give you one.

09:41.372 --> 09:43.332
But the reason Kaori died--

09:43.833 --> 09:46.502
Father-in-law, what are you talking about?

10:00.891 --> 10:02.810
Huh? Me?

10:21.537 --> 10:24.081
Thank goodness!

10:31.756 --> 10:33.257
It was around September, I think.

10:34.300 --> 10:36.510
Mr. Gojo actually came to see me himself,

10:37.386 --> 10:39.555
and asked me to look after you.

10:40.473 --> 10:44.185
So I had no choice, but to put on an act.

10:44.769 --> 10:45.936
An act?

10:46.646 --> 10:49.522
<i>"I had a bit of a bad feeling."</i>

10:49.523 --> 10:51.441
If anything were to happen to me,

10:51.442 --> 10:54.195
I want you, Yuta, to handle
the current first and second years.

10:54.695 --> 10:56.906
Hakari should be fine on his own.

10:57.615 --> 11:00.451
If something happens…
Did you fool around with a lady?

11:02.161 --> 11:04.872
Grown a sense of humor, huh, Yuta?

11:05.373 --> 11:06.665
No, it’s just that

11:06.666 --> 11:09.460
it's hard to imagine
something happening to you.

11:10.920 --> 11:13.296
<i>Especially that first year boy,
Yuji Itadori.</i>

11:13.297 --> 11:15.173
<i>He’s like you.</i>

11:15.174 --> 11:17.134
<i>He already had
a secret execution decided once.</i>

11:17.760 --> 11:19.720
<i>I would appreciate it
if you looked after him.</i>

11:21.597 --> 11:22.597
What about Miguel?

11:22.598 --> 11:24.558
He says he doesn’t want to see you.

11:26.852 --> 11:29.771
Rather than appointing another executioner

11:29.772 --> 11:32.315
or cutting off information about you,

11:32.316 --> 11:34.860
I figured that acting like this
was the best option.

11:35.611 --> 11:37.445
Well, we aren’t idiots either,

11:37.446 --> 11:40.949
so in exchange for being recognized
as the executioner by the higher-ups,

11:40.950 --> 11:42.742
I made a binding vow

11:42.743 --> 11:44.994
to kill you.

11:44.995 --> 11:47.873
So I did kill you. I’m really sorry.

11:50.876 --> 11:54.296
No… Then why am I alive?

11:55.381 --> 11:57.091
Reverse cursed technique.

11:58.384 --> 12:00.635
<i>I healed your heart instantly</i>

12:00.636 --> 12:03.305
<i>with reverse cursed technique
the moment it stopped.</i>

12:04.140 --> 12:07.852
<i>I thought it would work, because I heard
you did something similar before.</i>

12:08.352 --> 12:09.811
<i>Not many people know</i>

12:09.812 --> 12:12.857
<i>that I can output
positive energy directly.</i>

12:13.607 --> 12:18.320
Yes. This is the second time
your death has been faked.

12:18.988 --> 12:22.241
It might get found out soon,
but given the situation for now,

12:23.159 --> 12:24.659
your execution should be processed

12:24.660 --> 12:27.496
as already carried out.

12:29.957 --> 12:32.460
Why would you go that far for me?

12:33.002 --> 12:35.838
Because the people I care about

12:36.505 --> 12:38.424
care about you.

12:41.385 --> 12:46.014
I once carried power
far greater than myself.

12:46.015 --> 12:49.350
But the power I thought was forced on me

12:49.351 --> 12:51.853
was something I brought upon myself.

12:51.854 --> 12:56.233
That’s different from you.
The power you carry is not your own.

12:59.445 --> 13:01.280
You’re not at fault.

13:07.286 --> 13:11.248
That’s not it.
It’s not about blame or fault…

13:11.957 --> 13:14.418
- I killed--
- Itadori.

13:19.590 --> 13:21.383
- Fushiguro.
- What are you doing?

13:22.426 --> 13:23.802
We’re going back to Jujutsu High.

13:24.553 --> 13:26.430
The barrier around the school is weakened.

13:27.097 --> 13:30.809
As long as no one sees your face directly,
it won’t be a problem if you return.

13:31.519 --> 13:33.979
- Once you regroup with the others--
- Stop!

13:35.731 --> 13:37.858
Don’t just accept me like it’s nothing.

13:39.109 --> 13:40.945
Don’t pretend it never happened.

13:42.863 --> 13:45.407
I killed people…

13:47.409 --> 13:48.993
Because of me, people died!

13:48.994 --> 13:50.371
It's our fault!

13:51.997 --> 13:54.457
<i>Of course, you would say that.</i>

13:54.458 --> 13:55.668
Don’t decide on your own

13:56.835 --> 13:58.379
to give up.

14:11.850 --> 14:13.519
We’re not heroes.

14:14.562 --> 14:15.854
We’re jujutsu sorcerers.

14:16.564 --> 14:19.400
There’s no one who can truly judge us.

14:20.359 --> 14:21.610
That’s exactly why

14:22.236 --> 14:24.822
we have to keep proving
that we deserve to exist.

14:26.156 --> 14:28.366
<i>That’s not it, Fushiguro.</i>

14:28.367 --> 14:30.869
We don’t have time to sit around
worrying about ourselves.

14:30.870 --> 14:32.996
<i>- So you--</i>
- We must keep on

14:32.997 --> 14:34.247
helping people.

14:34.248 --> 14:37.000
<i>-As long as I’m by your side--</i>
- This was

14:37.001 --> 14:38.501
- your guiding principle, from the start.
<i>- Yes.</i>

14:38.502 --> 14:41.171
<i>-You'll suffer for the rest of your life!!</i>
- Then start by saving me,

14:42.047 --> 14:42.965
Itadori.

14:47.553 --> 14:49.013
A killing game by Noritoshi Kamo,

14:49.597 --> 14:52.308
forcing those granted jujutsu
to slaughter one another.

14:53.309 --> 14:54.560
The Culling Game.

14:56.103 --> 14:58.647
Tsumiki has been dragged
into the Culling Game too.

15:00.858 --> 15:03.277
Please, Itadori.

15:09.617 --> 15:11.493
<i>We need your strength.</i>

15:19.001 --> 15:23.588
CULLING GAME
GENERAL PROVISIONS

15:23.589 --> 15:24.589
CULLING GAME
GENERAL PROVISIONS

15:24.590 --> 15:25.257
WITHIN 19 DAYS
ENTER

15:26.300 --> 15:27.176
BREAK THE RULE, TECHNIQUE, CONFISCATE

15:27.968 --> 15:28.636
ENTER THE COLONY, PARTICIPATE

15:29.929 --> 15:30.512
END ONE'S LIFE

15:31.555 --> 15:32.056
SORCERER IS FIVE POINTS

15:32.640 --> 15:33.514
NON-SORCERER IS ONE POINT

15:33.515 --> 15:34.390
‎A SORCERER MUST ENTER THE GAME WITHIN
‎19 DAYS AFTER AWAKENING THEIR TECHNIQUE

15:34.391 --> 15:35.308
‎ANY WHO VIOLATES THE RULES
‎WILL BE CONFISCATED OF THEIR TECHNIQUE

15:35.309 --> 15:36.225
‎A NON-PLAYER BECOMES A PLAYER
‎WHEN THEY ENTER THE COLONY.

15:36.226 --> 15:37.185
‎PLAYERS EARN POINTS BY KILLING OTHERS.
‎ADMINISTRATOR ASSIGNS POINTS.

15:37.186 --> 15:38.102
‎IN PRINCIPLE,
‎5 FOR SORCERERS, 1 FOR NON-SORCERERS.

15:38.103 --> 15:38.938
‎THE GAME MASTER MUST APPROVE
‎THE RULE UNLESS IT HINDERS THE GAME

15:44.026 --> 15:46.695
Please, Itadori.

15:47.446 --> 15:49.281
We need your strength.

15:51.492 --> 15:52.618
Okkotsu.

15:53.661 --> 15:55.955
Sukuna is plotting something
using Fushiguro.

15:57.414 --> 16:00.083
Back in Shibuya,
when he took control of my body,

16:00.084 --> 16:02.753
it was probably because he force-fed me
several fingers at once.

16:03.420 --> 16:05.881
Right now, I have 15 fingers inside me.

16:06.465 --> 16:08.467
Even if the remaining five
were all eaten at once,

16:09.009 --> 16:12.221
I don’t think my body
would be taken over again.

16:13.097 --> 16:15.515
If I ever switch with Sukuna again,

16:15.516 --> 16:16.934
don’t hesitate. Kill me.

16:17.977 --> 16:19.436
I think you could do it.

16:21.563 --> 16:22.648
Got it.

16:23.482 --> 16:24.984
I’ll give it everything I’ve got.

16:26.151 --> 16:28.821
Fushiguro. What should I do?

16:30.197 --> 16:33.867
First, we go back to Jujutsu High
and make contact with Master Tengen.

16:37.079 --> 16:38.872
How do we undo the Prison Realm seal?

16:40.040 --> 16:43.627
What does Noritoshi Kamo want,
and what is he planning?

16:44.461 --> 16:46.714
The Culling Game
is an unprecedented jujutsu terror attack.

16:47.339 --> 16:50.384
To bring it under control,
we need answers to those two questions.

16:51.218 --> 16:54.388
The only one who can answer them
is Master Tengen.

16:55.222 --> 16:58.475
That person…
Tsukumo, does she know anything?

16:58.976 --> 17:00.728
I already talked to her.

17:01.395 --> 17:02.855
This was her idea.

17:03.647 --> 17:06.275
She’s currently hiding out
at Jujutsu High too.

17:07.860 --> 17:09.318
Hiding?

17:09.319 --> 17:11.697
She doesn’t want
anything to do with the higher-ups.

17:12.406 --> 17:16.035
The problem is Master Tengen’s
concealment barrier.

17:17.244 --> 17:20.456
<i>Out of over 1,000 doors
that constantly reshuffle,</i>

17:21.040 --> 17:23.291
<i>only one connects
to the Tombs of the Star Corridor</i>

17:23.292 --> 17:25.002
<i>where Master Tengen resides.</i>

17:26.795 --> 17:28.714
So unless we pick the right one,

17:29.214 --> 17:31.258
we can’t meet Master Tengen…

17:35.679 --> 17:36.847
Sorry, Fushiguro.

17:46.440 --> 17:47.775
I guess I have to ask now.

17:52.029 --> 17:53.405
What happened to Kugisaki?

18:00.913 --> 18:02.081
I see…

18:05.709 --> 18:06.627
Got it.

18:15.010 --> 18:16.011
Got it.

18:17.846 --> 18:19.598
That concealment barrier of his

18:20.182 --> 18:22.184
might actually be manageable.

18:23.560 --> 18:25.104
You were listening?

18:26.730 --> 18:28.315
What do you mean, Choso?

18:29.316 --> 18:33.112
Mahito once stole Sukuna’s fingers
and the Death Painting Wombs, didn’t he?

18:34.571 --> 18:36.698
We’ll do the same thing.

18:45.624 --> 18:48.085
Long time no see…
Guess it hasn’t been that long.

18:48.669 --> 18:50.087
Maki?

18:51.004 --> 18:51.839
Oh, hi.

18:52.798 --> 18:55.384
Maki, should you be moving around already?

18:55.968 --> 18:57.594
Yes. No problem.

18:58.178 --> 18:59.888
The burns were regrettable, but, oh well.

19:00.430 --> 19:02.391
Even the reverse cursed technique
leaves scars.

19:03.183 --> 19:06.103
As expected of a Heavenly Restriction
physical prodigy.

19:07.062 --> 19:09.897
At the very end,
it wasn’t resistance to curses,

19:09.898 --> 19:13.151
but sheer bodily durability
that separated life and death.

19:13.152 --> 19:15.404
It’s a shame about the clan head.

19:15.904 --> 19:18.407
I wasn’t competing or anything.

19:19.616 --> 19:22.578
Megumi, what's up with Tengen’s barrier?

19:23.412 --> 19:24.371
About that…

19:24.955 --> 19:26.206
I’ll explain.

19:27.166 --> 19:29.584
On the way from the doors
to the Tombs of the Star Corridor,

19:29.585 --> 19:31.878
there’s a vault where Jujutsu High

19:31.879 --> 19:33.130
keeps cursed tools and objects.

19:33.714 --> 19:36.048
Inside are the remains of my brothers.

19:36.049 --> 19:37.842
Noranso, Sho-oso,

19:37.843 --> 19:39.845
Tanso, Sanso, Kotsuso,

19:40.554 --> 19:42.055
and Shoso.

19:42.723 --> 19:44.849
Even as corpses,
with six of them together,

19:44.850 --> 19:47.059
the secondary effect of my technique

19:47.060 --> 19:48.854
should let me sense their presence.

19:51.273 --> 19:54.818
That’s fine and all, but who’s this guy?

19:58.322 --> 19:59.740
For now,

20:00.657 --> 20:02.950
he’s my brother, I guess.

20:02.951 --> 20:06.121
Yuji!

20:06.622 --> 20:07.581
Let’s go.

20:10.542 --> 20:11.376
There.

20:12.711 --> 20:14.045
No mistake.

20:14.046 --> 20:16.881
My brothers are resting beyond this point.

20:16.882 --> 20:17.883
- I’m opening it.
- Yes.

20:28.685 --> 20:29.770
Let’s head down.

20:31.396 --> 20:34.566
There’s an elevator that leads
to the Tombs of the Star Corridor.

20:36.276 --> 20:37.236
Choso.

20:38.195 --> 20:39.238
I know.

20:40.405 --> 20:43.825
I’ll come pick you up later.
Wait a little longer.

20:49.748 --> 20:52.292
Bloodstains? Did something happen?

20:53.085 --> 20:54.878
That was 12 years ago.

20:55.587 --> 20:56.754
Looking back,

20:56.755 --> 21:00.801
maybe all the distortions
started back then.

21:01.802 --> 21:04.638
All right, everyone.
The main hall is ahead.

21:21.655 --> 21:23.782
- There’s nothing here.
- This is the main hall?

21:24.491 --> 21:27.452
No. We’re being rejected.

21:28.328 --> 21:30.830
Tengen doesn’t interfere with reality,

21:30.831 --> 21:33.124
but with the Six Eyes sealed,

21:33.125 --> 21:35.918
I thought contact might be possible.

21:35.919 --> 21:37.337
Seems I underestimated him.

21:39.464 --> 21:41.883
The one being rejected isn’t all of us.

21:42.676 --> 21:44.052
Is it me?

21:46.221 --> 21:49.474
Should we head back?
Tsumiki doesn’t have much time.

21:52.311 --> 21:53.895
Leaving already?

21:55.147 --> 21:56.605
Nice to meet you.

21:56.606 --> 22:00.026
A child of the Zen'in clan,

22:00.027 --> 22:02.154
blood of Michizane, a Death Painting Womb…

22:04.823 --> 22:06.908
And the vessel of Sukuna.

23:41.545 --> 23:43.838
<i>I must set one condition.</i>

23:43.839 --> 23:45.589
<i>We came to ask
how to undo the Prison Realm.</i>

23:45.590 --> 23:47.174
<i>No greeting for me?</i>

23:47.175 --> 23:48.092
<i>So, the Culling Game…</i>

23:48.093 --> 23:49.844
<i>The forced evolution
of humanity across all of Japan.</i>

23:49.845 --> 23:51.137
<i>I think that, rule-wise,</i>

23:51.138 --> 23:52.138
<i>having your technique
confiscated equals death.</i>

23:52.139 --> 23:54.181
<i>If I switch places with Sukuna,
don't hesitate to kill me.</i>

23:54.182 --> 23:55.182
<i>Don't die.</i>

23:55.183 --> 23:55.976
‎NEXT EPISODE
